==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resplendency
<hw>Re*splen"den*cy</hw> <pr>(-d<it>e</it>n*s?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>resplendentia</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality
or state of being resplendent; brilliant luster; vivid brightness;
splendor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Son! thou in whom my glory I behold⟦br⟧
In full <qex>resplendence</qex>, heir of all my might.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>resplendency</qex> of his own almighty goodness.</q>
<rj><qau>Dr. J. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resplendent</ent>⟦br⟧
